Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan with a tight-fitting #lid.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling,
turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and
leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will
continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}(halved and sliced).

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1}(halved and sliced) and discard the core and seeds. Slice into
thin strips, then chop into thirds.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press).

Put the @Cornflour{10%g} into a large #bowl and season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}. Add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{390%g} and toss to coat
completely in the cornflour.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Pop your (now empty) #frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the chicken and fry until golden brown, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn every
~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the chicken has browned, lower the heat to medium and add the cooked veg back to
the frying pan.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan on high heat.

Once hot, add the sliced pepper and onion and season with @salt{} and @ground black
pepper{}. Stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. Transfer to a medium #bowl and set aside for
now.

== Sauce ==

Add the @Ketjap Manis{50%g}, @Rice Vinegar{30%ml}, @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp},
@Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{75%ml} to the pan.

Stir to combine and simmer, until the sauce has reduced slightly and the chicken is
cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Taste, and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed. Remove from the
heat.

> TIP: The sauce should be sticky, but add a splash more water if you'd like.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork and spoon into your #bowls.

Serve with the sticky chicken and veg on top.

Enjoy!